<topic id="adding-removing-a-master-file">
  <title>Adding or Removing Files in the Master Files Directory</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Master Files<indexterm>Add files</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Projects<indexterm>Master files<indexterm>Add
          files</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <section id="section_jvs_wfx_lnb">
      <title>Adding Files to the Master File Directory</title>
      <p>The <filepath>Master Files</filepath> directory only contains logical folders and linked
        files. To add files in the <filepath>Master Files</filepath> directory, use one of the
        following methods: <ul id="ul_u5x_xfx_lnb">
          <li>Right-click a file from your project and select <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/AddToMasterFiles16.png" id="image_v5x_xfx_lnb"/>Add to Master
              Files</uicontrol> from the contextual menu.</li>
          <li product="author developer editor">Select <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/AddFiles16.png" id="image_w5x_xfx_lnb"/>Add Files</uicontrol> or
                <uicontrol><image href="../img/AddSelectedFile16.png" id="image_gxg_p4h_5r"/>Add
              Edited File</uicontrol> from the contextual menu of the <filepath>Master
              Files</filepath> directory.</li>
          <li>Drag and drop files into the <filepath>Master Files</filepath> directory.</li>
          <li>From the contextual menu of the <xref
              href="xml-resource-hierarchy-view.dita#xml-resource-hierarchy-view"
                ><uicontrol>Resource Hierarchy Dependencies</uicontrol> view</xref>, use the
                <uicontrol><image href="../img/AddToMasterFiles16.png" id="image_x5x_xfx_lnb"/>Add
              to Master Files</uicontrol> action.</li>
        </ul></p>
      <p product="author developer editor">You can view the <term>master files</term> for the
        current resource by selecting <xref
          href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view/properties_files"
              ><uicontrol><image href="../img/DockableFrameProperties16.png" id="image_kqp_yfx_lnb"
            />Properties</uicontrol> from the contextual menu</xref> of the <xref
          href="../topics/using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
            ><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol> view</xref> and the <term>master files</term> for the
        current editor in the <xref href="viewing-file-properties.dita#viewing-file-properties"
            ><uicontrol>Properties</uicontrol></xref> and <xref
          href="view-status-information.dita#view-status-information"
            ><uicontrol>Information</uicontrol></xref> views.</p>
      <p product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">You can view the <term>master
          files</term> for the currently edited resource in the <xref
          href="viewing-file-properties.dita#viewing-file-properties"><uicontrol>Editor
            Properties</uicontrol> view</xref>.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_rkr_zfx_lnb">
      <title>Removing Files from the Master Files Directory</title>
      <p>The master files that are already defined in the project are automatically marked in the
        tree. To disable a master file, remove it from the <filepath>Master Files</filepath> folder
        (for example, use the <uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl+X</shortcut></uicontrol> or
            <uicontrol><shortcut>Delete</shortcut></uicontrol> keyboard shortcuts). Deleting files
        from the <filepath>Master Files</filepath> folder does NOT delete the files from disk. It
        just removes the logical files from that logical folder.</p>
    </section>
